J

js - package js
Contains no specific set of classes; any classes in here are designed to be used individually throughout a program.
js.dynamic - package js.dynamic
Contains classes related to dynamic data structures, such as Queues.
js.exception - package js.exception
Contains any custom Exceptions used by other JSLibrary classes.
js.preferences - package js.preferences
Contains classes which are used to create 'Preferences' windows, containing settings for the application which are saved automatically.
js.quiz - package js.quiz
 
js.uikit - package js.uikit
Contains classes designed to mimic elements from Apple's UIKit, which provide the UI elements for iOS.

JSConfirmDialogWithCheckbox - Class in js
Deprecated. JSConfirmDialogWithCheckbox has been deprecated because it's much easier and looks much nicer if you use JOptionPane. It turns out that the message parameter of JOptionPane.showMessageDialog can take an array of objects, which you can use to pass a String as the message and a JCheckBox together.
JSConfirmDialogWithCheckbox(String, String, String, String) - Constructor for class js.JSConfirmDialogWithCheckbox

JSTextFileReader - Class in js
Deprecated. JSTextFileReader has been deprecated in favour of the more fully-featured JSTextFileUtility, which supports writing to a file as well as reading from it. This class will be removed completely in JSLibrary 1.3.3.
JSTextFileReader(String) - Constructor for class js.JSTextFileReader
Deprecated. Creates a new JSTextFileReader from the specified file on disk.
JSTextFileReader(String, boolean) - Constructor for class js.JSTextFileReader
Deprecated. Creates a JSTextFileReader which allows the first line of the file to be skipped, since this often includes 'template' data which does not need to be read.
